commitMessage:
Bug 576230 - Code Clean Up "Use Autoboxing" changes program logic

Assume you have the following java code:

package bug;

public class Bug {
	public int something(int number) {
		return something(Integer.valueOf(number));
	}

	public int something(Integer number) {
		return number * 2;
	}
}

When I only select "Use Autoboxing" within the "Java Feature" tab, after
performing the clean up, I get the following source code:

package bug;

public class Bug {
	public int something(int number) {
		return something(number);
	}

	public int something(Integer number) {
		return number * 2;
	}
}

Change-Id: I9593a426daa7368e86cce62b03d6bd2aa2fe5086
Signed-off-by: Fabrice Tiercelin <fabrice.tiercelin@yahoo.fr>
Reviewed-on: https://git.eclipse.org/r/c/jdt/eclipse.jdt.ui/+/187485
Tested-by: JDT Bot <jdt-bot@eclipse.org>

dslRule:
/*!id: jdt.internal.javadoc.gethighlightpropertyvalue.to.getpropertyvalue*/
/*!description: Renames internal JavadocContentAccess2.getHighlightPropertyValue() to getPropertyValue() and updates its call site.*/
/*!severity: info*/
/*!minJavaVersion: 18*/
/*!tags: jdt, internal, refactoring*/
$call.getHighlightPropertyValue($prop, $tagProps) :: inClass("org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.text.javadoc.JavadocContentAccess2")
=> $call.getPropertyValue($prop, $tagProps)
;;

/*!id: jdt.internal.javadoc.stripliteral.condition.robustness*/
/*!description: Adjusts string length check in JavadocContentAccess2.stripQuotes() for robustness, changing > 2 to >= 2.*/
/*!severity: info*/
/*!minJavaVersion: 18*/
/*!tags: jdt, internal, bugfix*/
$str.length() > 2 :: inClass("org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.text.javadoc.JavadocContentAccess2") && inMethod("stripQuotes")
=> $str.length() >= 2
;;

/*!id: jdt.internal.problemslabeldecorator.remove-isaccessible-check*/
/*!description: Remove redundant IResource.isAccessible() check from UI-thread method for performance.*/
/*!severity: info*/
resource == null || !resource.isAccessible()
:: inClass("org.eclipse.jdt.ui.ProblemsLabelDecorator") && inMethod("computeContainerAdornmentFlags")
=> resource == null
;;
